# Contribution Workflow

## Commits

- Generate commit messages from the complete staged diff.
- Use `type(scope): imperative outcome`, for example `build(ci): validate pull requests`.
- Use `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `build`, `ci`, or `chore` as the type.
- Keep the subject concise and explain the reason in the body when it is not obvious.
- Never claim tests or checks that were not run.
- Keep unrelated changes in separate commits.

## Pull requests

- Always read `.github/pull_request_template.md` before drafting or creating a PR.
- Populate every section from the full branch diff and commit history.
- Check validation boxes only for commands that completed successfully.
- Record failed or unavailable checks under Testing evidence.
- Use `Not applicable` with a brief reason instead of deleting sections.
- Link related issues and ADRs so decisions remain traceable.
- Describe user impact, architecture changes, risk, rollback, and follow-up work concretely.
- Include screenshots or recordings for visible UI changes.
